  "prompt": "Septoplasty at fortis?",
  "response": "Fortis Healthcare is a well-known chain of hospitals in India, and they offer a wide range of medical services, including septoplasty. Septoplasty is a surgical procedure to correct a deviated septum, which is the displacement of the bone and cartilage that divides the two nostrils. This procedure can help improve breathing, reduce nasal congestion, and alleviate other related symptoms.\n\nIf you are considering septoplasty at a Fortis Hospital, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Consultation**: Schedule an appointment with an ENT specialist at Fortis. The doctor will evaluate your condition, discuss your symptoms, and determine if septoplasty is necessary.\n\n2. **Pre-operative Evaluation**: If septoplasty is recommended, you may undergo a series of pre-operative tests and evaluations to ensure you are fit for surgery.\n\n3. **Surgery**: The septoplasty procedure is usually performed under local or general anesthesia. It typically takes about 1-2 hours, depending on the complexity of the case.\n\n4. **Post-operative Care**: After the surgery, you will receive instructions on post-operative care, including medications, follow-up visits, and activities to avoid during the recovery period.\n\n5. **Recovery**: Recovery time varies from patient to patient, but most people can return to their normal activities within a few weeks.\n\nTo get more specific information about septoplasty at Fortis, including the cost, availability of specialized surgeons, and other details, you can visit the Fortis Healthcare website or contact the hospital directly.",
